data.chText: 事实；信息
data.enText: facts/information

data.chText: 细微之处；枝节；琐事
data.enText: a small individual fact or item; a less important fact or item

data.chText: 计划详尽的探险
data.enText: an expedition planned down to the last detail

data.chText: 他一动不动地站着，不放过街上的每一细微之处。
data.enText: He stood still, absorbing every detail of the street.

data.chText: 现在把要点告诉我，细节留到以后再说。
data.enText: Tell me the main points now; leave the details till later.

data.chText: 详情；全部细节
data.enText: the small facts or features of sth, when you consider them all together

data.chText: 这个问题将在下一章详细论述。
data.enText: This issue will be discussed in more detail in the next chapter.

data.chText: 研究工作一丝不苟地完成了。
data.enText: The research has been carried out with scrupulous attention to detail .

data.chText: 他很善于发现并记住细节。
data.enText: He had an eye for detail (= noticed and remembered small details) .

data.chText: 这个方案的具体细节尚需制订。
data.enText: The fine detail of the plan has yet to be worked out.

data.chText: 具体情况；（关于某事物的）资料，消息
data.enText: information about sth

data.chText: 请提供下列具体情况：姓名、年龄及性别。
data.enText: Please supply the following details: name, age and sex.

data.chText: 备有详细资料和订购单以供索取。
data.enText: Further details and booking forms are available on request.

data.chText: 他们没有提供这场比赛的具体情况。
data.enText: They didn't give any details about the game.

data.chText: “我们倒霉透了——”“唉呀，别给我细说了。”
data.enText: ‘We had a terrible time─’ ‘Oh, spare me the details (= don't tell me any more) .’

data.chText: 细部
data.enText: small parts

data.chText: （照片、绘画等的）细部，局部，次要部分
data.enText: a small part of a picture or painting; the smaller or less important parts of a picture, pattern, etc. when you consider them all together

data.chText: 这是透纳1844年水彩画的一小部分。
data.enText: This is a detail from the 1844 Turner painting.

data.chText: 一幅有很多细微之处的巨型画
data.enText: a huge picture with a lot of detail in it

data.chText: 士兵
data.enText: soldiers

data.chText: 特遣队；小分队；支队
data.enText: a group of soldiers given special duties
go into detail(s)

data.chText: 详细叙述；逐一说明
data.enText: to explain sth fully

data.chText: 我现在不能细说，太费工夫。
data.enText: I can't go into details now; it would take too long.

data.chText: 详述
data.enText: give facts/information

data.chText: 详细列举；详细说明；详述
data.enText: to give a list of facts or all the available information about sth

data.chText: 这本小册子详细介绍了当地所有旅馆及其设施。
data.enText: The brochure details all the hotels in the area and their facilities.

data.chText: 派遣士兵
data.enText: order soldier

data.chText: 派遣；选派；分遣
data.enText: to give an official order to sb, especially a soldier, to do a particular task

data.chText: 几名士兵被派组成一个搜索队。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+带to的不定式

data.enText: Several of the men were detailed to form a search party.

data.chText: 清洗汽车
data.enText: clean car

data.chText: 彻底清洗（汽车）
data.enText: to clean a car extremely thoroughly

data.chText: 他找到一个清洗汽车的临时工作。
data.enText: He got work for a while detailing cars.

simple_means.memory_skill: de 加强 + tail 剪，割，切 → 不断往下切分 → 细节

ex.chText: 警察叫她描述一下强盗的样子。
ex.enText: The police asked her to describe the robber.

ex.chText: 他描述了事故是如何发生的。
ex.enText: He described how the accident had happened.

ex.chText: 她在第6章里描述了伦敦之美。
ex.enText: She described the beauty of London in Chapter 6.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指说明某人或某事物的细节，使有清晰的形象。

ex.chText: 经理在报告中详述了下属员工在去年取得的进展。
ex.enText: In the report, the manager detailed the progress his staff had made over the last year.

ex.chText: 这种清洁剂的用法在小册子里有详细说明。
ex.enText: The usage of this cleanser is fully detailed in the brochure.

synonyms.bx: 指详细说明关于某事的事实或信息。

ex.chText: 请说明如何使用这台机器好吗？
ex.enText: Can you explain how the machine is operated?

ex.chText: 老师向孩子们说明规则。
ex.enText: The teacher explained the rules to the children.

synonyms.bx: 指以一种清楚明了的方式讲解某事。

ex.chText: 我想叙述一下我的生平。
ex.enText: I'd like to narrate my life story.
The story is narrated by the main actor.

data.enText: go into detail(s)

data.chText: 详细叙述；逐一说明
data.enText: to explain sth fully

data.chText: 我现在不能细说，太费工夫。
data.enText: I can't go into details now; it would take too long.

tr: an isolated fact that is considered separately from the whole
example: several of the details are similar
the essay contained too much detail

tr: a crew of workers selected for a particular task
example: a detail was sent to remove the fallen trees
the peacekeeping force includes one British contingent

tr: a small part that can be considered separately from the whole
example: it was perfect in all details
The ambulances were detailed to the fire station

value.boxr_value: The pronunciation /dɪ'teɪl/ is also used in American English. 美国英语亦读作 /dɪ'teɪl/。

value.def: The details of something are its individual features or elements.

example.ex: The details of the plan are still being worked out...
example.tran: 计划的细节仍在制订中。

example.ex: No details of the discussions have been given...
I recall every detail of the party.
example.tran: 我回想起聚会的每一个细节。

gramarinfo.label: usu with supp, oft N <l>of</l> n

value.def: Details about someone or something are facts or pieces of information about them.

example.ex: See the bottom of this page for details of how to apply for this exciting offer...
example.tran: 有关如何申请这一令人兴奋的工作的详情请参见本页底部。

example.ex: Full details will be announced soon.
example.tran: 具体信息很快就会公布。

value.def: A detail is a minor point or aspect of something, as opposed to the central ones.

example.ex: Only minor details now remain to be settled.
example.tran: 现在仅剩一些细枝末节的问题需要解决。

value.def: You can refer to the small features of something which are often not noticed as detail .

example.ex: We like his attention to detail and his enthusiasm.
example.tran: 我们喜欢他的细心和热情。

value.def: A detail of a picture is a part of it that is printed separately and perhaps made bigger, so that smaller features can be clearly seen.
If you detail things, you list them or give information about them.

example.ex: The report detailed the human rights abuses committed during the war.
example.tran: 这份报告详述了战争期间所发生的践踏人权的情况。

value.def: If someone is detailed to do a task or job, they are officially ordered to do it.

example.ex: He detailed a constable to take it to the Incident Room.
example.tran: 他派了一名警察把它送到重案调查室。

value.def: If someone does not go into details about a subject, or does not go into the detail, they mention it without explaining it fully or properly.

example.ex: He said he had been in various parts of Britain but did not go into details...
example.tran: 他说曾去过英国的许多地方，但没有细讲。

example.ex: Neither of them were prepared to go into the detail of their talks.
example.tran: 他们俩都没准备要详细说明他们会谈的情况。

value.def: If you examine or discuss something in detail, you do it thoroughly and carefully.

example.ex: We examine the wording in detail before deciding on the final text.
example.tran: 我们彻底仔细地检查了措词后才最终定稿。

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to cut 剪, 割, 切
rootsaffixes.title: tail

partsOfSpeech.dec: cur〔= curt 短〕+ tail 剪，割，切 → 剪短 → 缩短
curtail 缩短；削减 + ment 表名词 → 缩短；削减
de 加强 + tail 剪，割，切 → 不断往下切分 → 细节
en 使… + tail 剪，割，切 → 剪碎的东西让别人来收拾 → 使承担
re 一再 + tail 剪，割，切 → 一再均分单卖 → 零售
tail 剪，割，切 + or 表名词 → 裁缝
